{"name":"Approve requests with Telegram and Airtable","nodes":[{"parameters":{"formTitle":"Approve requests with Telegram and Airtable","formFields":{"values":[{"fieldLabel":"Email","requiredField":true},{"fieldLabel":"Role","requiredField":false},{"fieldLabel":"Stage","requiredField":false}]},"options":{"appendAttribution":false}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.formTrigger","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[-270,400],"id":"de6b1e00-56e3-4081-95b5-9f32a9eba820","name":"New Candidate Form Submission","webhookId":"f2e14451-a82a-4ba3-961d-0982146e03fd"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"2d9b08c1-bb5a-45d1-a09b-ef203ece1241","leftValue":"={{ $json.email }}","rightValue":"","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"notEmpty"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[54,400],"id":"9dc63e42-f919-4397-9be8-986ac79186af","name":"Required Fields Present?"},{"parameters":{"errorType":"errorMessage","errorMessage":"Missing required field 'email' on incoming candidate."},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stopAndError","typeVersion":1,"position":[54,910],"id":"3e80f397-2eda-4349-96d2-d4b16a631c87","name":"Abort — Malformed Input"},{"parameters":{"rules":{"values":[{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"79330ecc-6214-492f-8c95-b51da3295ace","leftValue":"={{ $json.kind || $json.type || 'standard' }}","rightValue":"auto-approve","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"equals"}}],"combinator":"and"},"renameOutput":true,"outputKey":"auto-approve"},{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"5dc5d117-6bee-46b7-a1b7-48f26f4932ae","leftValue":"={{ $json.kind || $json.type || 'standard' }}","rightValue":"needs-review","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"equals"}}],"combinator":"and"},"renameOutput":true,"outputKey":"needs-review"}]},"options":{"fallbackOutput":"extra"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.switch","typeVersion":3.2,"position":[378,400],"id":"4a9f921a-600e-4a3b-ad15-0cc9f2a5b277","name":"Route by Work Type"},{"parameters":{"operation":"upsert","base":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"HR & Recruitment Base"},"table":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Candidates"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":["candidateId"],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.airtable","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[702,130],"id":"262b5f9b-795a-4b6e-9642-8c387f25d3fd","name":"Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#hr","cachedResultName":"#hr"},"text":"=🚀 Priority candidate handled: {{ $json.candidateId }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[1026,640],"id":"c3752fad-5b3a-4c15-9f0e-b61fd1e1252b","name":"Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"create","base":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"HR & Recruitment Base"},"table":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Candidates"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.airtable","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[1350,1150],"id":"5bdd5124-0961-442d-9c98-d581e8a62dd5","name":"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"append","numberInputs":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.merge","typeVersion":3.2,"position":[1998,400],"id":"716bffc3-0c48-4ec0-b93c-e8fdaad3a0f8","name":"Merge Routed Work"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup","sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"query","value":"={{ $json.email }}"}]},"options":{"timeout":15000}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[2970,400],"id":"9f7247b5-76e0-461e-bd28-18f9be80776c","name":"Enrich with Reference Data","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"2c1883c6-d311-4ecd-ab95-6e2ad5049886","name":"enrichedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"89703673-7f2d-4566-9ab7-b719e0e4f89d","name":"enrichmentSource","value":"reference-api","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[3294,400],"id":"204e0d81-743a-44e0-b68d-51f53c712bfc","name":"Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"operation":"getCurrentDate","outputFieldName":"completedAt","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.dateTime","typeVersion":2,"position":[3618,400],"id":"4dd298c5-b61e-4ff4-8ad3-a5d0717db23f","name":"Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"dataToSave":{"values":[{"key":"runId","value":"={{ $execution.id }}"},{"key":"itemCount","value":"={{ $items().length }}"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.executionData","typeVersion":1,"position":[3942,400],"id":"5e8ef220-19b0-4846-b958-f010cc3a4e7c","name":"Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Build a stable idempotency key per candidate (djb2 hash, no deps)\nfunction hash(s) {\n  let h = 5381;\n  for (let i = 0; i < s.length; i++) h = ((h << 5) + h + s.charCodeAt(i)) >>> 0;\n  return h.toString(16);\n}\nreturn $input.all().map(item => {\n  const j = item.json;\n  return { json: { ...j, idempotencyKey: hash([j.candidateId, j.email].join('|')) } };\n});"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[4266,400],"id":"7fdd87fb-4cff-4ddd-8d4f-c42dc62e2441","name":"Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"operation":"removeItemsSeenInPreviousExecutions","logic":"removeItemsWithAlreadySeenKeyValues","dedupeValue":"={{ $json.idempotencyKey }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.removeDuplicates","typeVersion":2,"position":[4590,400],"id":"ab692f3b-6c0f-48bb-b936-9f47f198218f","name":"Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"operation":"csv","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.convertToFile","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[4914,400],"id":"9d253117-4de2-4f2f-aae5-b39fba00cea7","name":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Candidate Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5238,400],"id":"b55ace93-1a7d-4a9c-b28b-1a2549d4bd47","name":"Archive Row Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"47c73515-5482-4fe1-9990-d8d74fc1b370","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"9bac09b4-e076-473a-88d5-7a034bfa99a2","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"936ffb0e-b062-44d3-9a89-e276e4fe62a0","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5562,400],"id":"196975b9-e6dd-4fe5-a3e4-12c991135911","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Candidate Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5886,400],"id":"cc13a78d-e6fa-49b7-97ca-8530f3a734a6","name":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#hr","cachedResultName":"#hr"},"text":"=✅ Approve requests with Telegram and Airtable — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6210,400],"id":"177cf3e6-369f-4a9d-86ab-88d9ba4cf6d8","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"485ed7b1-e0c5-4e69-abf3-b011849aadf0","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"c908311d-e950-4576-8147-127e6aa8eda4","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"d4b147b0-ae64-4e4e-ad5c-59d991ac6657","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5562,1420],"id":"89771b54-7d18-4b29-95fe-94e47c4ad518","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"chatId":"={{ $json.chatId || 'OPS_CHAT_ID' }}","text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","additionalFields":{"appendAttribution":false}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.telegram","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[5886,1420],"id":"a3153536-19c6-4c7e-8965-e816ae52ba24","name":"Escalate Failure to Telegram","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"create","base":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"HR & Recruitment Base"},"table":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Candidates"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.airtable","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[6210,1420],"id":"127ae32a-546e-4d51-8052-19511ffee16b","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### New Candidate Form Submission\n\nServes an n8n-hosted form (Email, Role, Stage). Each submission becomes one execution.\n\nNext: Required Fields Present?","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"7b95e298-5cfa-61a2-c664-798e5f7e40d4","name":"Note: New Candidate Form Submission"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Required Fields Present?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.email }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Route by Work Type · ②→ Abort — Malformed Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"25034345-193d-b0f8-76ac-bbdfaf81b830","name":"Note: Required Fields Present?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Abort — Malformed Input\n\nFails fast with a clear message; triggers the error workflow instead of processing bad data.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,1030],"id":"9d4edeed-9f63-8a5b-ea68-e6f571ff8ff8","name":"Note: Abort — Malformed Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Work Type\n\nRoutes each item to one of 3 lanes: auto-approve, needs-review + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable · ②→ Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert · ③→ Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"1c27244d-be20-f530-9185-459c5e43792e","name":"Note: Route by Work Type"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable\n\nUpserts into Airtable's 'Candidates' table, matched on `candidateId` — safe to re-run without creating duplicates.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,250],"id":"c4da20f7-9832-ed6d-4ea3-f707b0e5678f","name":"Note: Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#hr`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,760],"id":"232b8462-cb3f-530b-3607-7235ea5cb51e","name":"Note: Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)\n\nCreates a new record in Airtable's 'Candidates' table.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,1270],"id":"a8474ce2-ae13-9fb9-bfcc-4e5e090e2d57","name":"Note: Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Routed Work\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,520],"id":"6c5cf7d3-bd50-de0a-4678-7621c07c41cb","name":"Note: Merge Routed Work"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"fb0f15b4-6179-2b28-6e1c-2d6fc3148cee","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"acc7c869-2166-2350-619b-09380619c21a","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"49734ef3-86e0-6cd5-ad6a-0ec779f647a8","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"e9a482a6-c51e-c4a8-f4a6-7a7b419d823b","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per candidate (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"ccbe58aa-c600-0e49-38c2-3b02816de4ec","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"fdbfd7b4-0719-00c4-fbbd-ebb1ca48f397","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"65304eea-a9ef-2940-d7d7-d095bdbb82a6","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nAppends a new row to 'Candidate Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Summarize Run Stats · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"30d08e07-a4fb-24b9-bc32-b4e69a86c306","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"ffb06657-20db-8b7b-bf26-42108dd5f039","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Candidate Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"ed556454-ffd4-b355-1566-a209a6078cb0","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#hr`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"cd762004-f3bd-e88f-dae2-9cf5fc154f27","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Telegram","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,1540],"id":"a420adee-322e-bc15-da72-875379f15068","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Telegram\n\nSends a Telegram message to the configured chat — the same bot can also receive replies, so this doubles as a two-way ops channel.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Telegram bot token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,1540],"id":"3f386bf1-880d-fed7-4f48-bd4e174e458f","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Telegram"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates a new record in Airtable's 'Candidates' table.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,1540],"id":"db748654-3ad3-f949-fc1b-6906cf649584","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Approve requests with Telegram and Airtable\n\n**Pattern:** Approval Workflow · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nApprove requests with Telegram and Airtable. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual screening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Candidate Form Submission → Required Fields Present? → Route by Work Type → Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable → Merge Routed Work → Enrich with Reference Data → Fold In Enrichment Fields → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to approval workflow without manual effort\n- Anyone automating screening in human resources\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"0750058c-12da-3ea8-7f7a-8c52c61e5a2c","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nUnrecognized work types are parked in a dead-letter lane instead of erroring the whole run or silently dropping the item — new event kinds will show up eventually, and this is where you'd notice one without losing it. One kind is deliberately routed through a sub-workflow to show how heavier per-type logic can be extracted without touching this router at all.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"5bc637a2-eef4-7dfe-7174-4f1ed3a9edf0","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAlready production-grade — deepen your understanding:\n\n1. Send a work-type value that matches no switch rule and confirm it lands in the dead-letter branch.\n2. Add a new work type and its own handling branch.\n3. Replace the direct-write branch with a sub-workflow call, matching the pattern already used for the first kind.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"76683011-3007-5da5-9d87-208cfec98a03","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"5719ab57-7ef3-168a-83fb-025a582771f0","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"86bcd3c4-a6bd-74a3-a468-de2e15d5517f","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your screening process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"40c54358-cc09-1d62-a30f-95ea77772bb1","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Candidate Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Required Fields Present?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Required Fields Present?":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Work Type","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Abort — Malformed Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Work Type":{"main":[[{"node":"Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Process 'auto-approve' → Airtable":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fast-Track 'needs-review' + Alert":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)":{"main":[[{"node":"Merge Routed Work","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Merge Routed Work":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Telegram","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Telegram":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"New Candidate Form Submission":[{"json":{"candidateId":"CAND-441","email":"sam.okafor@example.com","role":"Backend Engineer","stage":"Phone Screen"}},{"json":{"candidateId":"CAND-442","email":"priya.nair@example.com","role":"Product Designer","stage":"Final Interview"}}]},"versionId":"b66900fb-6e48-458f-8937-8b9394fedb93","id":"FDX10391"}